      "role": "user",
      "content": "that makes sense. but i've heard some legal experts argue that the \"living document\" idea is actually pretty dangerous because it lets judges just make up new rights that aren't in the text. they say we should stick to the original meaning or just focus on the specific procedures laid out by law. how would you respond to those critics?",
